Happy New Year (Nyepi) from Bali 🐒 
Today I want to give thanks to this beautiful island & it’s people for always welcoming & providing me such a wonderful home away from home for the past 2.5 years 🥰 
Nyepi is the Bali day of silence- meaning complete silence (no fire/light/electricity, no work, travelling- even the international airport shuts down, no entertainment & fasting) 
Its a very special time to be here on the island & witness this celebration as the island is purified 🙏🏼 #Bali #Indonesia #Nyepi

Steamy mornings as we watched the sunrise over 3 different countries, @anantara_goldentriangle is in the far north of Thailand boarding Laos & Myanmar, such a unique place in this world 💛

A warm welcome to the Golden Triangle by these gentle giants 🐘 @anantara_goldentriangle
I’m so thankful to have learnt so much about the complicated topic of captive elephants in Thailand, there’s so much more depth to the issue than we see on the surface, and I truely admire the work @anantara_goldentriangle & @gtaef_thailand are doing for the cause! It was my first visit to the north of Thailand & I wanted to visit an elephant camp that I would feel confident in their ethics, If you have the opportunity to visit this resort I certainly recommend, but also if you are visiting other camps/ sanctuaries be sure to research as much as you can before you visit! There’s more information on their websites
